Sentencas: In this study, sulfur tolerance of a conventional Ni-yttria stabilized zirconia (Ni-YSZ) anode for solid oxide fuel cells is significantly improved by surface modification.
Titulo: Enhancing Sulfur Tolerance of a Ni-YSZ Anode through BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.1Yb0.1O3-δ Infiltration

Sentencas: The Ni-YSZ anode modified by the infiltration of BaZr(0.1)Ce(0.7)Y(0.1)Yh(0.1)O(3-delta) (BZCYYb) demonstrates stable performance in a sulfur-containing H-2 fuel over 500 hours.
Titulo: Enhancing Sulfur Tolerance of a Ni-YSZ Anode through BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.1Yb0.1O3-δ Infiltration

Sentencas: In contrast, the bare Ni-YSZ anode without surface modification degrades drastically when exposed to the sulfur-containing H-2 fuel.
Titulo: Enhancing Sulfur Tolerance of a Ni-YSZ Anode through BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.1Yb0.1O3-δ Infiltration

Sentencas: This implies that the BZCYYb coating is an excellent catalyst for surface modification of the conventional Ni-YSZ anode.
Titulo: Enhancing Sulfur Tolerance of a Ni-YSZ Anode through BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.1Yb0.1O3-δ Infiltration

Sentencas: A single step infiltration of BZCYYb into the Ni-YSZ anode was sufficient to provide good sulfur tolerance.
Titulo: Enhancing Sulfur Tolerance of a Ni-YSZ Anode through BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.1Yb0.1O3-δ Infiltration
